review_blob: Bottle - hazy orange pour with good head. Aroma of sour yeast, notes of citrus and cherry. Mild flavor, but good. A bit heavier mouthfeel than a Duvel.
Bottle - Dark amber pour with little head. Aroma of dark & sour fruits: figs, raisins, cherries. Taste is like aroma, slightly metallic. Good beer!

Bottle - hazy orange amber pour with ok head. Aroma of cherries, butterscotch, and dark fruit. Flavor is like aroma, a bit sour and a touch soapy. Mouthfeel is a bit thick, ok carbonation. Good beer, not fantastic.
Bottle - Deep amber pour with good head. Sour yeast aroma, a bit floral. Taste is like aroma with notes of dark caramel. Good carbonation, slight bit syrupy.

Bottle - Golden orange pour with great head.  Aroma is mostly of sweet toasted barley.  Flavor is like aroma with sweetness from the barley up front and hops in the back.  Was expecting more hops and not as much much barley sweetness, but still a good beer.

Bottle - Dark reddish brown pour no head.  Aroma of banana bread with a bit if dark dried fruits.  Flavor is a bit off, not bad but notes of spice I can't place along with banana and clove.  Mouthfeel is good.  Good beer, not great.

Bottle - Deep burgundy brown, very little head.  Aroma of dried fruit, dates and figs.  Slight rich yeasty notes.  Flavor has notes from aroma and a bitterness that balances the sweetness.  Good carbonation but mouthfeel is a bit syrupy, although not as much as other comparably giant beers.  A well done huge beer!

Bottle - Dark amber pour with good head.  Aroma has the expected hoppy citrus notes, but also a surprising smokyness almost like a porter.  Flavor is good with the smoke coming through, mouthfeel is good.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Wet Hop IPA - Northern Hemisphere

review_blob: Bottle - Smells scuzzy, tastes scuzzy.  Why is there so much sediment in my IPA?  Probably the worst IPA I've ever had.
Bottle - Popped open like champagne, whoa!  Golden pour with great head.  Aroma of sour yeast and bananas.  Flavor has peppery and citrus notes, and notes from aroma.  Good mouthfeel and carbonation.
Bottle - Black pour with decent head.  Aroma of hops and toasted grain.  Flavor is bitter from hops and then bitter from the roasty toasty malts, hint of citrus.  Good mouthfeel and carbonation.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: Bottle - Hazy golden orange with great head.  Yeast aroma with notes of banana.  Flavor is dry and yeasty, very bubbly.
Bottle - Golden orange pour with great head.  Aroma of bananas, vanilla, and spice.  Yeasty flavor, with notes from aroma.  Mouthfeel decent.
Bottle, 1 year aged - Reddish brown pour with great head.  Aroma is yeasty, not much else going on.  Taste of toasted cereal and yeast, good carbonation and mouthfeel.  Not the greatest Belgian.

Draft - Dark brown pour with descent ivory head.  Aroma of toasted cereal and grain, bit of sweetness and hops too.  Flavor is like aroma, toasted and hoppy, very good.  Mouthfeel is a bit thick but decent carbonation helps.

Bottle - Dark brown with little head.  Aroma of cream and chocolate and berries, unexpected and nice.  Flavor is a tad sour and bitter, with notes of chocolate, yeast and toasted grain.  Mouthfeel is nice with good carbonation.
Bottle - Black with little ivory head.  Aroma of prunes, cloves, and toasted grains.  Taste of banana and clove, good mouth feel and carbonation.
Bottle - Hazy orange/amber pour with no head.  Aroma of honey and grains.  Taste like aroma, with toasted bitterness.  Mouthfeel a bit syrupy and not very bubbly.  Decent.

Bottle - dark amber with no head.  Strong aroma of raisins and dark syrup.  Flavor is like aroma, good but just too strong and syrupy.  Mouth feel is not great, very little carbonation.  Probably pretty good aged a few years.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Bottle, ruthless cork!  Hazy golde color with ok head, fizzled out quick.  Aroma of bananas and sourdough, mild floral notes.  Taste is like aroma, not too strong.  Pretty good.
Bottle - Black with ivory head that dissipates quick.  Aroma of dark dried fruits, figs, toffee.  Flavor is good, slightly bitter with notes from aroma.  Good!
Bottle - Golden orange, slightly hazy, no head.  Moderate hoppy aroma, not as prominent as many IPAs.  Taste is good and crisp, but slightly lacking.  Decent but nothing special.
Bottle - Reddish brown, no head.  Toasted malty aroma, decent.  Flavor has toasted cereal notes, but also is kinda sour/bitter; a bit off.  Not worth trying again.
Draft - Very hoppy with mild citrus.  More heavy and bitter than I prefer.  Good strong IPA, but not fantastic.
Bottle - Deep amber with big head that disappeared quick.  Slight sour cherries in the aroma, hint of banana.  Spicy notes and banana in flavor, ok beer.
Bottle - Dark brown pour, very little head.  Smells like Grapenuts cereal.  Little sour/bitterness in flavor, ok beer.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Bottle - Light hazy orange pour with fantastic head.  Moderate hoppy smell, bit of citrus.  Bitter citrus notes, decent IPA.
UPDATED: OCT 27, 2012
Bottle - Deep amber with ok head. Sweet yeasty aroma with hint of cherry. Dry and bubbly, tastes like the nose.  All in all, pretty good Belgian.
Very deep burgundy brown color with great head.  Very strong sour yeasty aroma.  Flavor is quite sour and a bit hoppier than the regular Abt 12.  Not as good as the regular.
Aroma is quite strong, hoppy and rich as hell.  Standard IPA appearance, a little darker though.  Flavor is fantastic, well balanced for such a strong IPA.  Great!
Dark in color and the aroma is nice and malty.  Flavor is nice and malty but a slight sourness detectable.  Decent
Very deep amber pour with decent head.  Aroma is mild but good, sour and slightly fruity.  Flavor is yeasty and sour with a dark maltiness.  Very good.  Palate is nice too, not too thick like the 12.
Hazy golden color with decent head.  Aroma is slightly sour and fruity.  Flavor is well balanced between sweet and bitter, a little extra sour.  Quite bubbly.  Not bad.
Very deep amber pour with decent head.  Aroma is mild but good, dark and sour.  Flavor is yeasty and sour with a dark maltiness.  Very good.  Palate is nice too, not too thick like the 12.
Amber color with nice head for an IPA.  Strong hoppy aroma.  Flavor is hoppy but also sweet.  Decent.
UPDATED: OCT 22, 2012
Very deep burgundy brown with good head.  Aroma is malty and nice.  Flavor is smooth, a bit slightly sweet with a dry finish.  Pretty decent beer.

Medium to dark amber color with ok head.  Aroma is quite strong, sour fruits and quite interesting.  Flavor is quite strange, like sweet ans sour fruits.  Probably not that bad but doesnt really taste like beer.
Clear golden color with not too much head.  Sweet yeasty aroma.  Milldly sweet and yeasty in flavor.  A bit more heavy than expected.
UPDATED: JAN 20, 2007
Golden color with little head.  Sour and slightly fruity aroma.  Flavor is decent.  Sour, slightly sweet with honey and slightly bitter.  Interesting.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: Clear orange color with no head.  Nice fruity aroma.  Flavor is a bit sour and fruity with a decent finish.  Not too bad.
UPDATED: MAY 1, 2007
Golden color with little head.  Sour aroma.  Flavor is standard west coast pale, hoppy and crisp.
UPDATED: JAN 30, 2007
Cloudy orange pour with moderate head.  Aroma is sweet with a bit of orange and citrus.  Flavor is smooth and a bit fruity.  Decent dry finish.  Pretty good.
Dec 2006 release.  Reddish amber color with decent head.  Slightly sour and fruity aroma.  Flavor is pretty sweet and heavy, very strong.  Mild finish.
Black with little head.  Mile aroma, kinda sweet and malty.  Flavor is pretty rich, malty with barley.  Very good.
Fizzy golden with lots of head.  Slightly sour and fruity aroma.  Light fruity flavor.  Not bad.
